1. SPRING AMQP
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Spring AMQP ek Spring library hai.

Jab hum following dependency add karte hain:

spring-boot-starter-amqp

to hume RabbitMQ ke saath kaam karne ke liye bahut saare high-level abstractions mil jaate hain, jaise:

- RabbitTemplate
- @RabbitListener
- Queue
- Exchange
- Binding
- Message Converters etc.

Ye abstractions hume RabbitMQ ke low-level implementation details se bachate hain.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. RABBITMQ JAVA CLIENT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RabbitMQ company khud ek Java library provide karti hai,
jise RabbitMQ Java Client kaha jaata hai.

Ye actual communication layer hai jo RabbitMQ Broker ke saath
communicate karti hai.

Iske major responsibilities hain:

- TCP connection establish karna
- Channels create aur manage karna
- Messages publish karna
- Messages consume karna
- ACK/NACK bhejna
- AMQP frames send aur receive karna

Spring AMQP internally isi RabbitMQ Java Client ko use karti hai.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. AMQP PROTOCOL
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

AMQP (Advanced Message Queuing Protocol) ek messaging protocol hai.

Jaise web communication ke liye HTTP protocol use hota hai,
waise hi RabbitMQ communication ke liye AMQP protocol use karta hai.

RabbitMQ Java Client RabbitMQ Broker ke saath directly Java method calls ke through communicate nahi karta.

Instead, RabbitMQ Java Client:

* Application se aane wale operations (publish message, consume message, ACK, NACK, queue declaration, exchange declaration, etc.) ko AMQP protocol ke according AMQP frames me convert karta hai.
* In AMQP frames ko TCP connection ke through RabbitMQ Broker ko bhejta hai.

Similarly, RabbitMQ Broker bhi responses ko AMQP frames ke form me RabbitMQ Java Client ko bhejta hai.
RabbitMQ Java Client un AMQP frames ko receive karke unhe Java objects/events me convert karta hai aur unhe Spring AMQP ya application tak pahucha deta hai.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. CHANNEL 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Channel ek lightweight virtual connection hota hai jo TCP connection ke andar create kiya jata hai.

RabbitMQ ke almost saare operations:

- Publish Message
- Consume Message
- ACK
- NACK
- Queue Declare
- Exchange Declare
- Binding Create

Channel ke through hi hote hain.

=> Channel Ki Zarurat Kyu Padi?

Suppose channels exist nahi karte.

To har producer aur consumer ko RabbitMQ se baat karne ke liye:

Alag TCP Connection banana padta.

Example:

Producer-1  -> TCP Connection
Producer-2  -> TCP Connection
Consumer-1  -> TCP Connection
Consumer-2  -> TCP Connection
Consumer-3  -> TCP Connection

Problem:

TCP Connection banana expensive hota hai.

- TCP handshake lagta hai
- Memory lagti hai
- Network resources lagte hain

RabbitMQ Ka Solution

Ek TCP Connection banao.

Uske andar multiple Channels banao.

                TCP Connection
                       |
        --------------------------------
        |              |              |
        v              v              v
    Channel-1      Channel-2      Channel-3

Ab:

Producer-1 -> Channel-1

Consumer-1 -> Channel-2

Consumer-2 -> Channel-3

Sab same TCP connection share kar sakte hain.

